NATION BRIEFS																																												 New Delhi, Nov. 29 (PTI): Delhi High Court today pulled up Jawaharlal Nehru University for its medieval thinking and showing prejudice by denying admission to an MPhil aspirant for allegedly raising his voice against caste-based harassment on the campus.																																												Directing the university to admit Amritashva Kamal within two weeks, Justice Ravinder. S. Bhatt also slapped a litigation cost of Rs 25,000 on it. The money will be paid to Kamal, a Scheduled Caste candidate. 																																												Kamal was not allowed to enter the premises for the interview because before appearing in the written exam, he had filed a complaint to the authorities over harassment of SC students. 																																												New Delhi (PTI): The home ministry has sent IPS officer Kiran Bedis application for voluntary retirement to the personnel and training department. The Centre is likely to approve her request by Tuesday. 																																												Jammu (PTI): Auxiliary police in Jammu and Kashmir will be given special training to deal with disaster management. Two companies, one each at Jammu and Srinagar, will be formed for this purpose.																																												New Delhi (PTI): The Red Fort became a world heritage site with Unesco handing over the certificate at a ceremony at the Diwan-i-Khas on Thursday. The fort is the 27th Indian site to receive the tag.																																												Chennai (PTI): A lady teacher of a private school was arrested on the charge of beating up a student. Selvasankari allegedly hit Arafat, a Class VIII student of the school at Kothavalchavadi, with a ruler after he refused to do class work and insisted on having his lunch. The boy suffered an injury on his forehead. The teacher has been granted bail. 																																												 Bangalore (PTI): The Karnataka Assembly has been dissolved, ending the political uncertainty in the state. Raj Bhavan received the presidential notification on Wednesday night.
